</para>
<para>The geometric information (bounds, frame) of the Layer is used as the &quot;box&quot; in which the text is drawn. The <ref refid="group___text_layer" kindref="compound">TextLayer</ref> also has a number of other properties that influence how the text is drawn. Most important of these properties are: a pointer to the string to draw itself, the font, the text color, the background color of the layer, the overflow mode and alignment of the text inside the layer. <simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="group___layer" kindref="compound">Layers</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
